Sean R. Meyer

Bio

I am currently a Senior Scientist at the Michigan Institute for Data Science. My experience includes developing predictive models, engineering features, designing databases and data pipelines, and building business intelligence deliverables. During my doctoral work, I co-authored and applied an open-source framework to expedite development to prepare time-series clinical data for predictive modeling. The framework reduces time spent manually preparing data and facilitates multidisciplinary research team communication through a common language. I have been a military intelligence officer in the Army Reserve and served in the Base Defense Operations Center (BDOC) at HQ Resolute Support, Kabul, AF. I was responsible for collecting, integrating, and communicating intelligence. Before my doctoral work and military deployment, I was a Senior Business Intelligence (BI) Analyst at the U-M School of Dentistry. In this role, I pioneered the BI initiative for the school, meeting with leadership at the associate dean and department chair level and providing full-stack analytical solutions.

Education

PhD | Design Science | University of Michigan

MS | Design Science | University of Michigan

MBA | Business Administration, Enterprise Business Intelligence | Eastern Michigan University

BS | Computer Science | Eastern Michigan University

AAS | Interactive Web Design | Washtenaw Community College

Experience

Doctoral Student | College of Engineering, University of Michigan | Sept 2017 - August 2021

Battle Captain | U.S. Army | July 2016 – June 2017

Senior Business Intelligence Analyst | School of Dentistry, University of Michigan | March 2012 – July 2016
